ASSEMBLY JOINT RESOLUTION—Urging Congress to extend
the Social Security Fairness Act.
1 WHEREAS, The Social Security Fairness Act was signed into law
2 on January 5, 2025, thereby repealing the Government Pension
3 Offset and the Windfall Elimination Provision; and
4 WHEREAS, The Social Security Fairness Act applies to monthly
5 Social Security benefits affected by the Government Pension Offset
6 and Windfall Elimination Provision from December 2023 forward;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, The repeal of the Government Pension Offset
9 restored benefits to an estimated 9 out of 10 public employees who
10 lost their entire spousal benefit under the Government Pension
11 Offset formula, regardless of whether such employee’s spouse paid
12 Social Security taxes; and
13 WHEREAS, The repeal of the Windfall Elimination Provision
14 stopped the reduction of Social Security benefits for employees who
15 have earned a federal, state or local government pension and who
16 have, at some point, been employed in jobs where the employees
17 were required to pay Social Security taxes and paid said taxes for
18 the period required to qualify for such benefits; and
19 WHEREAS, More than 2 million government employees and
20 retirees across the United States of America now benefit from the
21 repeal of the Government Pension Offset or the Windfall
22 Elimination Provision; and
