1 WHEREAS, Up to 11.8 percent of Social Security beneficiaries in
2 Nevada affected by the Windfall Elimination Provision are expected
3 to receive an estimated increase to their duly earned Social Security
4 benefits of up to $558 per month; and
5 WHEREAS, Social Security benefit recipients affected by the
6 Government Pension Offset will receive an estimated increase to
7 their monthly Social Security benefits of between $700 and $1,190;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, Social Security benefit recipients are expected to
10 receive an estimated $4,320 in backdated payments of benefits for
11 the months of January 2024 to December 2024 alone; now,
12 therefore, be it
13 RESOLVED BY THE ASSEMBLY AND SENATE OF THE STATE OF
14 NEVADA, JOINTLY, That the Nevada Legislature hereby urges
15 Congress to enact legislation to extend the Social Security Fairness
16 Act to apply from the month of December 2013 forward and for the
17 President of the United States to sign that legislation into law; and
18 be it further
19 RESOLVED, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly prepare and
20 transmit a copy of this resolution to the President of the United
21 States, the Vice President of the United States as the presiding
22 officer of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of Representatives
23 and each member of the Nevada Congressional Delegation; and be it
24 further
25 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
26 passage.
